
// This Hyperlambda code snippet replaces all occurrences of the carriage return character ("\r") in the value of the node referenced by [.dp] with a space (" "). The [strings.replace] slot is used to perform the replacement operation, where the first argument specifies the target character to replace, and the second argument specifies the replacement character. The expression [x:@.dp/#] is used to reference the value of the [.dp] node.
strings.replace:x:@.dp/#
   .:"\r"
   .:" "
